Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and finely chop @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Trim ends from @zucchini{1}; working over a large #bowl{} and using a #peeler{}, shave zucchini lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go. Stop once you get to the seedy core; discard core.

Toss zucchini ribbons with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and 1 tsp lemon zest. Season with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{} and add juice from 1 lemon wedge. Toss to coat. Set aside.

== Ravioli ==

Once water is boiling, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%oz} to #pot{}. Reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside. Keep empty pot handy for next step.

== Tomato Cream Sauce ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water until combined and creamy. Stir in @sugar{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp}.

Add as much remaining lemon zest as you like and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Add drained ravioli to pot with sauce; gently stir to coat. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide ravioli between bowls and top with zucchini ribbons and @almonds{1/2%oz}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: Toast almonds before serving for a nuttier flavor.